						               													<description>Inspired by the video game TETRIS, except you play this version with the use of dice. Each turn you roll 6 colored dice and place them on the drop zone. Instead of having the shapes fall, you will be trying to arrange the dice to fall and make the shapes.  There are five colored dice that will be used to match all the similar colored shapes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As each new shape is discovered, you will be trying to match the dice to these shapes before they move off the board and generate a new shape.  Each shape you match with the dice causes the dice to be removed from the board and the other dice to fall down into their place.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You start the 1 minute timer. You can use six actions to manipulate the dice to help you line them up and create stacks to generate the shapes. If you run out of time, the dice fall as they are.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Try to create as many shapes as possible to collect the highest score.  Be careful with your actions because if you leave too many dice on the board, they may start to stack too high and cause you to lose the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
